obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (10873)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10873&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Right to Information`
  line `Act, 2005.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) of section 4, sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 5, sections 12,`
  line `13, 15,16, 24, 27 and 28 shall come into force at once, and the remaining provisions of this Act shall`
  line `come into force on the one hundred and twentieth day of its enactment.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (10874)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10874&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate Government" means in relation to a public authority which is established,`
  line `constituted, owned, controlled or substantially financed by funds provided directly or indirectly--`
  line
  line `(i) by the Central Government or the Union territory administration, the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) by the State Government, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) "Central Information Commission" means the Central Information Commission constituted`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(c) "Central Public Information Officer" means the Central Public Information Officer designated`
  line `under sub-section (1) and includes a Central Assistant Public Information Officer designated as such`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) "Chief Information Commissioner" and "Information Commissioner" mean the Chief`
  line `Information Commissioner and Information Commissioner appointed under sub-section (3) of section`
  line 12;
  line
  line `(e) "competent authority" means--`
  line
  line `(i) the Speaker in the case of the House of the People or the Legislative Assembly of a State`
  line `or a Union territory having such Assembly and the Chairman in the case of the Council of States`
  line `or Legislative Council of a State;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Chief Justice of India in the case of the Supreme Court;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Chief Justice of the High Court in the case of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(iv) the President or the Governor, as the case may be, in the case of other authorities`
  line `established or constituted by or under the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(v) the administrator appointed under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(f) "information" means any material in any form, including records, documents, memos, e-mails,`
  line `opinions, advices, press releases, circulars, orders, logbooks, contracts, reports, papers, samples,`
  line `models, data material held in any electronic form and information relating to any private body which`
  line `can be accessed by a public authority under any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act by the appropriate Government or`
  line `the competent authority, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(h) "public authority" means any authority or body or institution of self- government established`
  line `or constituted--`
  line
  line `(a) by or under the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) by any other law made by Parliament;`
  line
  line `(c) by any other law made by State Legislature;`
  line
  line `(d) by notification issued or order made by the appropriate Government,`
  line
  line `and includes any--`
  line
  line `(i) body owned, controlled or substantially financed;`
  line
  line `(ii) non-Government organisation substantially financed,`
  line
  line `directly or indirectly by funds provided by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(i) "record" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) any document, manuscript and file;`
  line
  line `(b) any microfilm, microfiche and facsimile copy of a document;`
  line
  line `(c) any reproduction of image or images embodied in such microfilm (whether enlarged or`
  line `not); and`
  line
  line `(d) any other material produced by a computer or any other device;`
  line
  line `(j) "right to information" means the right to information accessible under this Act which is held`
  line `by or under the control of any public authority and includes the right to--`
  line
  line `(i) inspection of work, documents, records;`
  line
  line `(ii) taking notes, extracts or certified copies of documents or records;`
  line
  line `(iii) taking certified samples of material;`
  line
  line `(iv) obtaining information in the form of diskettes, floppies, tapes, video cassettes or in any`
  line `other electronic mode or through printouts where such information is stored in a computer or in`
  line `any other device;`
  line
  line `(k) "State Information Commission" means the State Information Commission constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(l) "State Chief Information Commissioner" and "State Information Commissioner" mean the`
  line `State Chief Information Commissioner and the State Information Commissioner appointed under subsection`
  line `(3) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(m) "State Public Information Officer" means the State Public Information Officer designated`
  line `under sub-section (1) and includes a State Assistant Public Information Officer designated as such`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(n) "third party" means a person other than the citizen making a request for information and`
  line `includes a public authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (10875)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Right to information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10875&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, all citizens shall have the right to`
  line information.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (10876)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Obligations of public authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10876&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every public authority shall--`
  line
  line `(a) maintain all its records duly catalogued and indexed in a manner and the form which`
  line `facilitates the right to information under this Act and ensure that all records that are appropriate to be`
  line `computerised are, within a reasonable time and subject to availability of resources, computerised and`
  line `connected through a network all over the country on different systems so that access to such records`
  line `is facilitated;`
  line
  line `(b) publish within one hundred and twenty days from the enactment of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) the particulars of its organisation, functions and duties;`
  line
  line `(ii) the powers and duties of its officers and employees;`
  line
  line `(iii) the procedure followed in the decision making process, including channels of supervision`
  line `and accountability;`
  line
  line `(iv) the norms set by it for the discharge of its functions;`
  line
  line `(v) the rules, regulations, instructions, manuals and records, held by it or under its control or`
  line `used by its employees for discharging its functions;`
  line
  line `(vi) a statement of the categories of documents that are held by it or under its control;`
  line
  line `(vii) the particulars of any arrangement that exists for consultation with, or representation by,`
  line `the members of the public in relation to the formulation of its policy or implementation thereof;`
  line
  line `(viii) a statement of the boards, councils, committees and other bodies consisting of two or`
  line `more persons constituted as its part or for the purpose of its advice, and as to whether meetings of`
  line `those boards, councils, committees and other bodies are open to the public, or the minutes of such`
  line `meetings are accessible for public;`
  line
  line `(ix) a directory of its officers and employees;`
  line
  line `(x) the monthly remuneration received by each of its officers and employees, including the`
  line `system of compensation as provided in its regulations;`
  line
  line `(xi) the budget allocated to each of its agency, indicating the particulars of all plans, proposed`
  line `expenditures and reports on disbursements made;`
  line
  line `(xii) the manner of execution of subsidy programmes, including the amounts allocated and`
  line `the details of beneficiaries of such programmes;`
  line
  line `(xiii) particulars of recipients of concessions, permits or authorisations granted by it;`
  line
  line `(xiv) details in respect of the information, available to or held by it, reduced in an electronic`
  line form;
  line
  line `(xv) the particulars of facilities available to citizens for obtaining information, including the`
  line `working hours of a library or reading room, if maintained for public use;`
  line
  line `(xvi) the names, designations and other particulars of the Public Information Officers;`
  line
  line `(xvii) such other information as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `and thereafter update these publications every year;`
  line
  line `(c) publish all relevant facts while formulating important policies or announcing the decisions`
  line `which affect public;`
  line
  line `(d) provide reasons for its administrative or quasi-judicial decisions to affected persons.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be a constant endeavour of every public authority to take steps in accordance with the`
  line `requirements of clause (b) of sub-section (1) to provide as much information suo motu to the public at`
  line `regular intervals through various means of communications, including internet, so that the public have`
  line `minimum resort to the use of this Act to obtain information.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-section (1), every information shall be disseminated widely and in such`
  line `form and manner which is easily accessible to the public.`
  line
  line `(4) All materials shall be disseminated taking into consideration the cost effectiveness, local language`
  line `and the most effective method of communication in that local area and the information should be easily`
  line `accessible, to the extent possible in electronic format with the Central Public Information Officer or State`
  line `Public Information Officer, as the case may be, available free or at such cost of the medium or the print`
  line `cost price as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-sections (3) and (4), "disseminated" means making known or`
  line `communicated the information to the public through notice boards, newspapers, public announcements,`
  line `media broadcasts, the internet or any other means, including inspection of offices of any public authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (10877)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Designation of Public Information Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10877&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every public authority shall, within one`
  line `hundred days of the enactment of this Act, designate as many officers as the Central Public Information`
  line `Officers or State Public Information Officers, as the case may be, in all administrative units or offices`
  line `under it as may be necessary to provide information to persons requesting for the information under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), every public authority shall designate an`
  line `officer, within one hundred days of the enactment of this Act, at each sub-divisional level or other subdistrict`
  line `level as a Central Assistant Public Information Officer or a State Assistant Public Information`
  line `Officer, as the case may be, to receive the applications for information or appeals under this Act for`
  line `forwarding the same forthwith to the Central Public Information Officer or the State Public Information`
  line `Officer or senior officer specified under sub-section (1) of section 19 or the Central Information`
  line `Commission or the State Information Commission, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an application for information or appeal is given to a Central Assistant Public`
  line `Information Officer or a State Assistant Public Information Officer, as the case may be, a period of five`
  line `days shall be added in computing the period for response specified under sub-section (1) of section 7.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be,`
  line `shall deal with requests from persons seeking information and render reasonable assistance to the persons`
  line `seeking such information.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be,`
  line `may seek the assistance of any other officer as he or she considers it necessary for the proper discharge of`
  line `his or her duties.`
  line
  line `(5) Any officer, whose assistance has been sought under sub-section (4), shall render all assistance to`
  line `the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, seeking`
  line `his or her assistance and for the purposes of any contravention of the provisions of this Act, such other`
  line `officer shall be treated as a Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (10878)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Request for obtaining information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10878&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person, who desires to obtain any information under`
  line `this Act, shall make a request in writing or through electronic means in English or Hindi or in the official`
  line `language of the area in which the application is being made, accompanying such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed, to--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may`
  line `be, of the concerned public authority;`
  line
  line `(b) the Central Assistant Public Information Officer or State Assistant Public Information Officer,`
  line `as the case may be,`
  line
  line `specifying the particulars of the information sought by him or her:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such request cannot be made in writing, the Central Public Information Officer`
  line `or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, shall render all reasonable assistance to the`
  line `person making the request orally to reduce the same in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) An applicant making request for information shall not be required to give any reason for`
  line `requesting the information or any other personal details except those that may be necessary for contacting`
  line him.
  line
  line `(3) Where an application is made to a public authority requesting for an information,--`
  line
  line `(i) which is held by another public authority; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the subject matter of which is more closely connected with the functions of another public`
  line authority,
  line
  line `the public authority, to which such application is made, shall transfer the application or such part of it as`
  line `may be appropriate to that other public authority and inform the applicant immediately about such`
  line `transfer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the transfer of an application pursuant to this sub-section shall be made as soon as`
  line `practicable but in no case later than five days from the date of receipt of the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (10879)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Disposal of request.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10879&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the proviso to sub-section (2) of section 5 or the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 6, the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as`
  line `the case may be, on receipt of a request under section 6 shall, as expeditiously as possible, and in any case`
  line `within thirty days of the receipt of the request, either provide the information on payment of such fee as`
  line `may be prescribed or reject the request for any of the reasons specified in sections 8 and 9:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the information sought for concerns the life or liberty of a person, the same shall`
  line `be provided within forty-eight hours of the receipt of the request.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be,`
  line `fails to give decision on the request for information within the period specified under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `deemed to have refused the request.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a decision is taken to provide the information on payment of any further fee representing`
  line `the cost of providing the information, the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information`
  line `Officer, as the case may be, shall send an intimation to the person making the request, giving--`
  line
  line `(a) the details of further fees representing the cost of providing the information as determined by`
  line `him, together with the calculations made to arrive at the amount in accordance with fee prescribed`
  line `under sub-section (1), requesting him to deposit that fees, and the period intervening between the`
  line `despatch of the said intimation and payment of fees shall be excluded for the purpose of calculating`
  line `the period of thirty days referred to in that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(b) information concerning his or her right with respect to review the decision as to the amount of`
  line `fees charged or the form of access provided, including the particulars of the appellate authority, time`
  line `limit, process and any other forms.`
  line
  line `(4) Where access to the record or a part thereof is required to be provided under this Act and the`
  line `person to whom access is to be provided is sensorily disabled, the Central Public Information Officer or`
  line `State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, shall provide assistance to enable access to the`
  line `information, including providing such assistance as may be appropriate for the inspection.`
  line
  line `(5) Where access to information is to be provided in the printed or in any electronic format, the`
  line `applicant shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (6), pay such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fee prescribed under sub-section (1) of section 6 and sub-sections (1) and (5) of`
  line `section 7 shall be reasonable and no such fee shall be charged from the persons who are of below poverty`
  line `line as may be determined by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (5), the person making request for the`
  line `information shall be provided the information free of charge where a public authority fails to comply with`
  line `the time limits specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(7) Before taking any decision under sub-section (1), the Central Public Information Officer or State`
  line `Public Information Officer, as the case may be, shall take into consideration the representation made by a`
  line `third party under section 11.`
  line
  line `(8) Where a request has been rejected under sub-section (1), the Central Public Information Officer or`
  line `State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, shall communicate to the person making the`
  line request,--
  line
  line `(i) the reasons for such rejection;`
  line
  line `(ii) the period within which an appeal against such rejection may be preferred; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the particulars of the appellate authority.`
  line
  line `(9) An information shall ordinarily be provided in the form in which it is sought unless it would`
  line `disproportionately divert the resources of the public authority or would be detrimental to the safety or`
  line `preservation of the record in question.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (10880)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Exemption from disclosure of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10880&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,`
  line `there shall be no obligation to give any citizen,--`
  line
  line `(a) information, disclosure of which would prejudicially affect the sovereignty and integrity of`
  line `India, the security, strategic, scientific or economic interests of the State, relation with foreign State or`
  line `lead to incitement of an offence;`
  line
  line `(b) information which has been expressly forbidden to be published by any court of law or`
  line `tribunal or the disclosure of which may constitute contempt of court;`
  line
  line `(c) information, the disclosure of which would cause a breach of privilege of Parliament or the`
  line `State Legislature;`
  line
  line `(d) information including commercial confidence, trade secrets or intellectual property, the`
  line `disclosure of which would harm the competitive position of a third party, unless the competent`
  line `authority is satisfied that larger public interest warrants the disclosure of such information;`
  line
  line `(e) information available to a person in his fiduciary relationship, unless the competent authority`
  line `is satisfied that the larger public interest warrants the disclosure of such information;`
  line
  line `(f) information received in confidence from foreign Government;`
  line
  line `(g) information, the disclosure of which would endanger the life or physical safety of any person`
  line `or identify the source of information or assistance given in confidence for law enforcement or security`
  line purposes;
  line
  line `(h) information which would impede the process of investigation or apprehension or prosecution`
  line `of offenders;`
  line
  line `(i) cabinet papers including records of deliberations of the Council of Ministers, Secretaries and`
  line `other officers:`
  line
  line `Provided that the decisions of Council of Ministers, the reasons thereof, and the material on the`
  line `basis of which the decisions were taken shall be made public after the decision has been taken, and`
  line `the matter is complete, or over:`
  line
  line `Provided further that those matters which come under the exemptions specified in this section`
  line `shall not be disclosed;`
  line
  line `(j) information which relates to personal information the disclosure of which has no relationship`
  line `to any public activity or interest, or which would cause unwarranted invasion of the privacy of the`
  line `individual unless the Central Public Information Officer or the State Public Information Officer or the`
  line `appellate authority, as the case may be, is satisfied that the larger public interest justifies the`
  line `disclosure of such information:`
  line
  line `Provided that the information which cannot be denied to the Parliament or a State Legislature`
  line `shall not be denied to any person.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything in the Official Secrets Act, 1923 (19 of 1923) nor any of the`
  line `exemptions permissible in accordance with sub-section (1), a public authority may allow access to`
  line `information, if public interest in disclosure outweighs the harm to the protected interests.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of clauses (a), (c) and (i) of sub-section (1), any information relating to`
  line `any occurrence, event or matter which has taken place, occurred or happened twenty years before the date`
  line `on which any request is made under section 6 shall be provided to any person making a request under that`
  line `section:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any question arises as to the date from which the said period of twenty years has`
  line `to be computed, the decision of the Central Government shall be final, subject to the usual appeals`
  line `provided for in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (10881)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Grounds for rejection to access in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10881&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of section`
  line `8, a Central Public Information Officer or a State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, may`
  line `reject a request for information where such a request for providing access would involve an infringement`
  line `of copyright subsisting in a person other than the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (10882)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Severability.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10882&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a request for access to information is rejected on the ground that it is in`
  line `relation to information which is exempt from disclosure, then, notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Act, access may be provided to that part of the record which does not contain any information which is`
  line `exempt from disclosure under this Act and which can reasonably be severed from any part that contains`
  line `exempt information.`
  line
  line `(2) Where access is granted to a part of the record under sub-section (1), the Central Public`
  line `Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, shall give a notice to the`
  line `applicant, informing--`
  line
  line `(a) that only part of the record requested, after severance of the record containing information`
  line `which is exempt from disclosure, is being provided;`
  line
  line `(b) the reasons for the decision, including any findings on any material question of fact, referring`
  line `to the material on which those findings were based;`
  line
  line `(c) the name and designation of the person giving the decision;`
  line
  line `(d) the details of the fees calculated by him or her and the amount of fee which the applicant is`
  line `required to deposit; and`
  line
  line `(e) his or her rights with respect to review of the decision regarding non-disclosure of part of the`
  line `information, the amount of fee charged or the form of access provided, including the particulars of the`
  line `senior officer specified under sub-section (1) of section 19 or the Central Information Commission or`
  line `the State Information Commission, as the case may be, time limit, process and any other form of`
  line access.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (10883)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Third party information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10883&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Central Public Information Officer or a State Public`
  line `Information Officer, as the case may be, intends to disclose any information or record, or part thereof on a request made under this Act, which relates to or has been supplied by a third party and has been treated as`
  line `confidential by that third party, the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information`
  line `Officer, as the case may be, shall, within five days from the receipt of the request, give a written notice to`
  line `such third party of the request and of the fact that the Central Public Information Officer or State Public`
  line `Information Officer, as the case may be, intends to disclose the information or record, or part thereof, and`
  line `invite the third party to make a submission in writing or orally, regarding whether the information should`
  line `be disclosed, and such submission of the third party shall be kept in view while taking a decision about`
  line `disclosure of information:`
  line
  line `Provided that except in the case of trade or commercial secrets protected by law, disclosure may be`
  line `allowed if the public interest in disclosure outweighs in importance any possible harm or injury to the`
  line `interests of such third party.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a notice is served by the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information`
  line `Officer, as the case may be, under sub-section (1) to a third party in respect of any information or record`
  line `or part thereof, the third party shall, within ten days from the date of receipt of such notice, be given the`
  line `opportunity to make representation against the proposed disclosure.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 7, the Central Public Information Officer or State`
  line `Public Information Officer, as the case may be, shall, within forty days after receipt of the request under`
  line `section 6, if the third party has been given an opportunity to make representation under sub-section (2),`
  line `make a decision as to whether or not to disclose the information or record or part thereof and give in`
  line `writing the notice of his decision to the third party.`
  line
  line `(4) A notice given under sub-section (3) shall include a statement that the third party to whom the`
  line `notice is given is entitled to prefer an appeal under section 19 against the decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (10884)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Constitution of Central Information Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10884&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a body to be known as the Central Information Commission`
  line `to exercise the powers conferred on, and to perform the functions assigned to, it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Information Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Information Commissioner; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of Central Information Commissioners, not exceeding ten, as may be deemed`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Information Commissioner and Information Commissioners shall be appointed by the`
  line `President on the recommendation of a committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(i) the Prime Minister, who shall be the Chairperson of the committee;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Leader of Opposition in the Lok Sabha; and`
  line
  line `(iii) a Union Cabinet Minister to be nominated by the Prime Minister.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where the Leader of`
  line `Opposition in the House of the People has not been recognised as such, the Leader of the single largest`
  line `group in opposition of the Government in the House of the People shall be deemed to be the Leader of`
  line Opposition.
  line
  line `(4) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs of the Central Information`
  line `Commission shall vest in the Chief Information Commissioner who shall be assisted by the Information`
  line `Commissioners and may exercise all such powers and do all such acts and things which may be exercised`
  line `or done by the Central Information Commission autonomously without being subjected to directions by`
  line `any other authority under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chief Information Commissioner and Information Commissioners shall be persons of`
  line `eminence in public life with wide knowledge and experience in law, science and technology, social`
  line `service, management, journalism, mass media or administration and governance.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chief Information Commissioner or an Information Commissioner shall not be a Member of`
  line `Parliament or Member of the Legislature of any State or Union territory, as the case may be, or hold any`
  line `other office of profit or connected with any political party or carrying on any business or pursuing any`
  line profession.
  line
  line `(7) The headquarters of the Central Information Commission shall be at Delhi and the Central`
  line `Information Commission may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, establish offices at`
  line `other places in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (10885)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Terms of office and conditions of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10885&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Information Commissioner shall hold`
  line `office ^1[for such term as may be prescribed by the Central Government] and shall not be eligible for`
  line `reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Chief Information Commissioner shall hold office as such after he has attained the`
  line `age of sixty-five years.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Information Commissioner shall hold office ^1[for such term as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government] or till he attains the age of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier, and shall not be`
  line `eligible for reappointment as such Information Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that every Information Commissioner shall, on vacating his office under this sub-section be`
  line `eligible for appointment as the Chief Information Commissioner in the manner specified in sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 12:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Information Commissioner is appointed as the Chief Information`
  line `Commissioner, his term of office shall not be more than five years in aggregate as the Information`
  line `Commissioner and the Chief Information Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Information Commissioner or an Information Commissioner shall before he enters`
  line `upon his office make and subscribe before the President or some other person appointed by him in that`
  line `behalf, an oath or affirmation according to the form set out for the purpose in the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Information Commissioner or an Information Commissioner may, at any time, by`
  line `writing under his hand addressed to the President, resign from his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Information Commissioner or an Information Commissioner may be removed`
  line `in the manner specified under section 14.`
  line
  line `^2[(5) The salaries and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service of the Chief`
  line `Information Commissioner and the Information Commissioners shall be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the salaries, allowances and other conditions of service of the Chief Information`
  line `Commissioner or the Information Commissioners shall not be varied to their disadvantage after their`
  line `appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Chief Information Commissioner and the Information Commissioners`
  line `appointed before the commencement of the Right to Information (Amendment) Act, 2019 shall continue`
  line `to be governed by the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder as if the Right to Information`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2019 had not come into force.]`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government shall provide the Chief Information Commissioner and the Information`
  line `Commissioners with such officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient performance of`
  line `their functions under this Act, and the salaries and allowances payable to, and the terms and conditions of`
  line `service of the officers and other employees appointed for the purpose of this Act shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `Provided also that the salaries, allowances and other conditions of service of the Chief Information`
  line `Commissioner and the Information Commissioners shall not be varied to their disadvantage after their`
  line appointment.
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government shall provide the Chief Information Commissioner and the Information`
  line `Commissioners with such officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient performance of`
  line `their functions under this Act, and the salaries and allowances payable to and the terms and conditions of`
  line `service of the officers and other employees appointed for the purpose of this Act shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 2019, s. 2, for "for a term of five years from the date on which he enters upon his office"`
  line `(w.e.f. 24-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by, s. 2, ibid., for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 24-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (10886)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Removal of Chief Information Commissioner or Information Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10886&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (3), the Chief Information Commissioner or any Information Commissioner`
  line `shall be removed from his office only by order of the President on the ground of proved misbehaviour or`
  line `incapacity after the Supreme Court, on a reference made to it by the President, has, on inquiry, reported`
  line `that the Chief Information Commissioner or any Information Commissioner, as the case may be, ought on`
  line `such ground be removed.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may suspend from office, and if deem necessary prohibit also from attending the`
  line `office during inquiry, the Chief Information Commissioner or Information Commissioner in respect of`
  line `whom a reference has been made to the Supreme Court under sub-section (1) until the President has`
  line `passed orders on receipt of the report of the Supreme Court on such reference.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the President may by order remove from`
  line `office the Chief Information Commissioner or any Information Commissioner if the Chief Information`
  line `Commissioner or a Information Commissioner, as the case may be,--`
  line
  line `(a) is adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the President, involves moral`
  line `turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) engages during his term of office in any paid employment outside the duties of his office; or`
  line
  line `(d) is, in the opinion of the President, unfit to continue in office by reason of infirmity of mind or`
  line `body; or`
  line
  line `(e) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `the Chief Information Commissioner or a Information Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Chief Information Commissioner or a Information Commissioner in any way, concerned or`
  line `interested in any contract or agreement made by or on behalf of the Government of India or participates in`
  line `any way in the profit thereof or in any benefit or emolument arising therefrom otherwise than as a`
  line `member and in common with the other members of an incorporated company, he shall, for the purposes`
  line `of sub-section (1), be deemed to be guilty of misbehaviour.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (10887)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Constitution of State Information Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10887&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a body to be known as the ......... (name of the State)`
  line `Information Commission to exercise the powers conferred on, and to perform the functions assigned to, it`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Information Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the State Chief Information Commissioner, and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of State Information Commissioners, not exceeding ten, as may be deemed`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(3) The State Chief Information Commissioner and the State Information Commissioners shall be`
  line `appointed by the Governor on the recommendation of a committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(i) the Chief Minister, who shall be the Chairperson of the committee;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Leader of Opposition in the Legislative Assembly; and`
  line
  line `(iii) a Cabinet Minister to be nominated by the Chief Minister.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where the Leader of`
  line `Opposition in the Legislative Assembly has not been recognised as such, the Leader of the single largest`
  line `group in opposition of the Government in the Legislative Assembly shall be deemed to be the Leader of`
  line Opposition.
  line
  line `(4) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs of the State Information`
  line `Commission shall vest in the State Chief Information Commissioner who shall be assisted by the State`
  line `Information Commissioners and may exercise all such powers and do all such acts and things which may`
  line `be exercised or done by the State Information Commission autonomously without being subjected to`
  line `directions by any other authority under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Chief Information Commissioner and the State Information Commissioners shall be`
  line `persons of eminence in public life with wide knowledge and experience in law, science and technology,`
  line `social service, management, journalism, mass media or administration and governance.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Chief Information Commissioner or a State Information Commissioner shall not be a`
  line `Member of Parliament or Member of the Legislature of any State or Union territory, as the case may be,`
  line `or hold any other office of profit or connected with any political party or carrying on any business or`
  line `pursuing any profession.`
  line
  line `(7) The headquarters of the State Information Commission shall be at such place in the State as the`
  line `State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify and the State Information`
  line `Commission may, with the previous approval of the State Government, establish offices at other places in`
  line `the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
