obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Chief Information Commissioner shall`
  line `hold office ^1[for such term as may be prescribed by the Central Government] and shall not be eligible for`
  line `reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no State Chief Information Commissioner shall hold office as such after he has attained`
  line `the age of sixty-five years.`
  line
  line `(2) Every State Information Commissioner shall hold office ^1[for such term as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government] or till he attains the age of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier, and shall not be`
  line `eligible for reappointment as such State Information Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that every State Information Commissioner shall, on vacating his office under this subsection, be eligible for appointment as the State Chief Information Commissioner in the manner specified`
  line `in sub-section (3) of section 15:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the State Information Commissioner is appointed as the State Chief`
  line `Information Commissioner, his term of office shall not be more than five years in aggregate as the State`
  line `Information Commissioner and the State Chief Information Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Chief Information Commissioner or a State Information Commissioner, shall before he`
  line `enters upon his office make and subscribe before the Governor or some other person appointed by him in`
  line `that behalf, an oath or affirmation according to the form set out for the purpose in the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Chief Information Commissioner or a State Information Commissioner may, at any`
  line `time, by writing under his hand addressed to the Governor, resign from his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Chief Information Commissioner or a State Information Commissioner may`
  line `be removed in the manner specified under section 17.`
  line
  line `^2[(5) The salaries and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service of the State`
  line `Chief Information Commissioner and the State Information Commissioners shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the salaries, allowances and other conditions of service of the State Chief Information`
  line `Commissioner and the State Information Commissioners shall not be varied to their disadvantage after`
  line `their appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Chief Information Commissioner and the State Information`
  line `Commissioners appointed before the commencement of the Right to Information (Amendment) Act, 2019`
  line `shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this Act and the rules made there under as if the Right`
  line `to Information (Amendment) Act, 2019 had not come into force.]`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government shall provide the State Chief Information Commissioner and the State`
  line `Information Commissioners with such officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient`
  line `performance of their functions under this Act, and the salaries and allowances payable to and the terms`
  line `and conditions of service of the officers and other employees appointed for the purpose of this Act shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 2019, s. 3, for, "for a term of five years from the date on which he enters upon his office"`
  line `(w.e.f. 24-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 2019, s. 3, for sub-section (5), (w.e.f. 24-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (10889)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Removal of State Chief Information Commissioner or State Information Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10889&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), the State Chief Information Commissioner or a State`
  line `Information Commissioner shall be removed from his office only by order of the Governor on the ground`
  line `of proved misbehaviour or incapacity after the Supreme Court, on a reference made to it by the Governor,`
  line `has on inquiry, reported that the State Chief Information Commissioner or a State Information`
  line `Commissioner, as the case may be, ought on such ground be removed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor may suspend from office, and if deem necessary prohibit also from attending the`
  line `office during inquiry, the State Chief Information Commissioner or a State Information Commissioner in`
  line `respect of whom a reference has been made to the Supreme Court under sub-section (1) until the`
  line `Governor has passed orders on receipt of the report of the Supreme Court on such reference.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Governor may by order remove from`
  line `office the State Chief Information Commissioner or a State Information Commissioner if a State Chief`
  line `Information Commissioner or a State Information Commissioner, as the case may be,--`
  line
  line `(a) is adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Governor, involves moral`
  line `turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) engages during his term of office in any paid employment outside the duties of his office; or`
  line
  line `(d) is, in the opinion of the Governor, unfit to continue in office by reason of infirmity of mind or`
  line `body; or`
  line
  line `(e) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `the State Chief Information Commissioner or a State Information Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) If the State Chief Information Commissioner or a State Information Commissioner in any way,`
  line `concerned or interested in any contract or agreement made by or on behalf of the Government of the State`
  line `or participates in any way in the profit thereof or in any benefit or emoluments arising therefrom`
  line `otherwise than as a member and in common with the other members of an incorporated company, he`
  line `shall, for the purposes of sub-section (1), be deemed to be guilty of misbehaviour.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (10890)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers and functions of Information Commissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10890&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `it shall be the duty of the Central Information Commission or State Information Commission, as the case`
  line `may be, to receive and inquire into a complaint from any person,--`
  line
  line `(a) who has been unable to submit a request to a Central Public Information Officer or State`
  line `Public Information Officer, as the case may be, either by reason that no such officer has been`
  line `appointed under this Act, or because the Central Assistant Public Information Officer or State`
  line `Assistant Public Information Officer, as the case may be, has refused to accept his or her application`
  line `for information or appeal under this Act for forwarding the same to the Central Public Information`
  line `Officer or State Public Information Officer or senior officer specified in sub-section (1) of section 19`
  line `or the Central Information Commission or the State Information Commission, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) who has been refused access to any information requested under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) who has not been given a response to a request for information or access to information within`
  line `the time limit specified under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) who has been required to pay an amount of fee which he or she considers unreasonable;`
  line
  line `(e) who believes that he or she has been given incomplete, misleading or false information under`
  line `this Act; and`
  line
  line `(f) in respect of any other matter relating to requesting or obtaining access to records under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) Where the Central Information Commission or State Information Commission, as the case may`
  line `be, is satisfied that there are reasonable grounds to inquire into the matter, it may initiate an inquiry in`
  line `respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Information Commission or State Information Commission, as the case may be, shall,`
  line `while inquiring into any matter under this section, have the same powers as are vested in a civil court`
  line `while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and compel them to give oral or written`
  line `evidence on oath and to produce the documents or things;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and inspection of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing summons for examination of witnesses or documents; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything inconsistent contained in any other Act of Parliament or State`
  line `Legislature, as the case may be, the Central Information Commission or the State Information`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, may, during the inquiry of any complaint under this Act, examine any`
  line `record to which this Act applies which is under the control of the public authority, and no such record`
  line `may be withheld from it on any grounds.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (10891)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10891&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who, does not receive a decision within the time specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) or clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 7, or is aggrieved by a decision of the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, may within thirty days`
  line `from the expiry of such period or from the receipt of such a decision prefer an appeal to such officer who`
  line `is senior in rank to the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer as the case`
  line `may be, in each public authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that such officer may admit the appeal after the expiry of the period of thirty days if he or`
  line `she is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an appeal is preferred against an order made by a Central Public Information Officer or a`
  line `State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, under section 11 to disclose third party information,`
  line `the appeal by the concerned third party shall be made within thirty days from the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(3) A second appeal against the decision under sub-section (1) shall lie within ninety days from the`
  line `date on which the decision should have been made or was actually received, with the Central Information`
  line `Commission or the State Information Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Information Commission or the State Information Commission, as the case`
  line `may be, may admit the appeal after the expiry of the period of ninety days if it is satisfied that the`
  line `appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(4) If the decision of the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as`
  line `the case may be, against which an appeal is preferred relates to information of a third party, the Central`
  line `Information Commission or State Information Commission, as the case may be, shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard to that third party.`
  line
  line `(5) In any appeal proceedings, the onus to prove that a denial of a request was justified shall be on the`
  line `Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, who denied`
  line `the request.`
  line
  line `(6) An appeal under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be disposed of within thirty days of the`
  line `receipt of the appeal or within such extended period not exceeding a total of forty-five days from the date`
  line `of filing thereof, as the case may be, for reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(7) The decision of the Central Information Commission or State Information Commission, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be binding.`
  line
  line `(8) In its decision, the Central Information Commission or State Information Commission, as the case`
  line `may be, has the power to--`
  line
  line `(a) require the public authority to take any such steps as may be necessary to secure compliance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act, including--`
  line
  line `(i) by providing access to information, if so requested, in a particular form;`
  line
  line `(ii) by appointing a Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as`
  line `the case may be;`
  line
  line `(iii) by publishing certain information or categories of information;`
  line
  line `(iv) by making necessary changes to its practices in relation to the maintenance, management`
  line `and destruction of records;`
  line
  line `(v) by enhancing the provision of training on the right to information for its officials;`
  line
  line `(vi) by providing it with an annual report in compliance with clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) require the public authority to compensate the complainant for any loss or other detriment`
  line suffered;
  line
  line `(c) impose any of the penalties provided under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) reject the application.`
  line
  line `(9) The Central Information Commission or State Information Commission, as the case may be, shall`
  line `give notice of its decision, including any right of appeal, to the complainant and the public authority.`
  line
  line `(10) The Central Information Commission or State Information Commission, as the case may be,`
  line `shall decide the appeal in accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (10892)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10892&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1)Where the Central Information Commission or the State Information Commission,`
  line `as the case may be, at the time of deciding any complaint or appeal is of the opinion that the Central`
  line `Public Information Officer or the State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, has, without any`
  line `reasonable cause, refused to receive an application for information or has not furnished information`
  line `within the time specified under sub-section (1) of section 7 or malafidely denied the request for`
  line `information or knowingly given incorrect, incomplete or misleading information or destroyed information`
  line `which was the subject of the request or obstructed in any manner in furnishing the information, it shall`
  line `impose a penalty of two hundred and fifty rupees each day till application is received or information is`
  line `furnished, so however, the total amount of such penalty shall not exceed twenty-five thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Public Information Officer or the State Public Information Officer, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard before any penalty is imposed on`
  line `him:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the burden of proving that he acted reasonably and diligently shall be on the`
  line `Central Public Information Officer or the State Public Information Officer, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Central Information Commission or the State Information Commission, as the case`
  line `may be, at the time of deciding any complaint or appeal is of the opinion that the Central Public`
  line `Information Officer or the State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, has, without any`
  line `reasonable cause and persistently, failed to receive an application for information or has not furnished`
  line `information within the time specified under sub-section (1) of section 7 or malafidely denied the request`
  line `for information or knowingly given incorrect, incomplete or misleading information or destroyed`
  line `information which was the subject of the request or obstructed in any manner in furnishing the`
  line `information, it shall recommend for disciplinary action against the Central Public Information Officer or`
  line `the State Public Information Officer, as the case may be, under the service rules applicable to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (10893)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10893&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or`
  line `any rule made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (10894)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10894&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in the Official Secrets Act, 1923 (19 of 1923), and any other`
  line `law for the time being in force or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (10895)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10895&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No court shall entertain any suit, application or other proceeding`
  line `in respect of any order made under this Act and no such order shall be called in question otherwise than`
  line `by way of an appeal under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (10896)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Act not to apply to certain organisations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10896&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing contained in this Act shall apply to the`
  line `intelligence and security organisations specified in the Second Schedule, being organisations established`
  line `by the Central Government or any information furnished by such organisations to that Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the information pertaining to the allegations of corruption and human rights violations`
  line `shall not be excluded under this sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of information sought for is in respect of allegations of violation of`
  line `human rights, the information shall only be provided after the approval of the Central Information`
  line `Commission, and notwithstanding anything contained in section 7, such information shall be provided`
  line `within forty-five days from the date of the receipt of request.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Schedule by`
  line `including therein any other intelligence or security organisation established by that Government or`
  line `omitting therefrom any organisation already specified therein and on the publication of such notification,`
  line `such organisation shall be deemed to be included in or, as the case may be, omitted from the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(3) Every notification issued under sub-section (2) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in this Act shall apply to such intelligence and security organisation being`
  line `organisations established by the State Government, as that Government may, from time to time, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that the information pertaining to the allegations of corruption and human rights violations`
  line `shall not be excluded under this sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of information sought for is in respect of allegations of violation of`
  line `human rights, the information shall only be provided after the approval of the State Information`
  line `Commission and, notwithstanding anything contained in section 7, such information shall be provided`
  line `within forty-five days from the date of the receipt of request.`
  line
  line `(5) Every notification issued under sub-section (4) shall be laid before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (10897)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Monitoring and reporting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10897&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Information Commission or State Information`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, shall, as soon as practicable after the end of each year, prepare a report`
  line `on the implementation of the provisions of this Act during that year and forward a copy thereof to the`
  line `appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Ministry or Department shall, in relation to the public authorities within their jurisdiction,`
  line `collect and provide such information to the Central Information Commission or State Information`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, as is required to prepare the report under this section and comply with`
  line `the requirements concerning the furnishing of that information and keeping of records for the purposes of`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Each report shall state in respect of the year to which the report relates,--`
  line
  line `(a) the number of requests made to each public authority;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of decisions where applicants were not entitled to access to the documents`
  line `pursuant to the requests, the provisions of this Act under which these decisions were made and the`
  line `number of times such provisions were invoked;`
  line
  line `(c) the number of appeals referred to the Central Information Commission or State Information`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, for review, the nature of the appeals and the outcome of the appeals;`
  line
  line `(d) particulars of any disciplinary action taken against any officer in respect of the administration`
  line `of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the amount of charges collected by each public authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) any facts which indicate an effort by the public authorities to administer and implement the`
  line `spirit and intention of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) recommendations for reform, including recommendations in respect of the particular public`
  line `authorities, for the development, improvement, modernisation, reform or amendment to this Act or`
  line `other legislation or common law or any other matter relevant for operationalising the right to access`
  line information.
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, may, as soon as practicable`
  line `after the end of each year, cause a copy of the report of the Central Information Commission or the State`
  line `Information Commission, as the case may be, referred to in sub-section (1) to be laid before each House`
  line `of Parliament or, as the case may be, before each House of the State Legislature, where there are two`
  line `Houses, and where there is one House of the State Legislature before that House.`
  line
  line `(5) If it appears to the Central Information Commission or State Information Commission, as the case`
  line `may be, that the practice of a public authority in relation to the exercise of its functions under this Act`
  line `does not conform with the provisions or spirit of this Act, it may give to the authority a recommendation`
  line `specifying the steps which ought in its opinion to be taken for promoting such conformity.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (10898)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Appropriate Government to prepare programmes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10898&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, to`
  line `the extent of availability of financial and other resources,--`
  line
  line `(a) develop and organise educational programmes to advance the understanding of the public, in`
  line `particular of disadvantaged communities as to how to exercise the rights contemplated under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) encourage public authorities to participate in the development and organisation of`
  line `programmes referred to in clause (a) and to undertake such programmes themselves;`
  line
  line `(c) promote timely and effective dissemination of accurate information by public authorities`
  line `about their activities; and`
  line
  line `(d) train Central Public Information Officers or State Public Information Officers, as the case may`
  line `be, of public authorities and produce relevant training materials for use by the public authorities`
  line themselves.
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall, within eighteen months from the commencement of this Act,`
  line `compile in its official language a guide containing such information, in an easily comprehensible form`
  line `and manner, as may reasonably be required by a person who wishes to exercise any right specified in this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government shall, if necessary, update and publish the guidelines referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) at regular intervals which shall, in particular and without prejudice to the generality of`
  line `sub-section (2), include--`
  line
  line `(a) the objects of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the postal and street address, the phone and fax number and, if available, electronic mail`
  line `address of the Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may`
  line `be, of every public authority appointed under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner and the form in which request for access to an information shall be made to a`
  line `Central Public Information Officer or State Public Information Officer, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(d) the assistance available from and the duties of the Central Public Information Officer or State`
  line `Public Information Officer, as the case may be, of a public authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the assistance available from the Central Information Commission or State Information`
  line `Commission, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(f) all remedies in law available regarding an act or failure to act in respect of a right or duty`
  line `conferred or imposed by this Act including the manner of filing an appeal to the Commission;`
  line
  line `(g) the provisions providing for the voluntary disclosure of categories of records in accordance`
  line `with section 4;`
  line
  line `(h) the notices regarding fees to be paid in relation to requests for access to an information; and`
  line
  line `(i) any additional regulations or circulars made or issued in relation to obtaining access to an`
  line `information in accordance with this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government must, if necessary, update and publish the guidelines at regular`
  line intervals.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (10899)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to make rules by appropriate Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 2019, s. 4, (w.e.f. 24-10-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10899&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the cost of the medium or print cost price of the materials to be disseminated under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the fee payable under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the fee payable under sub-sections (1) and (5) of section 7;`
  line
  line `^1[(ca) the term of office of the Chief Information Commissioner and Information Commissioners`
  line `under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 13 and the State Chief Information Commissioner and State`
  line `Information Commissioners under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(cb) the salaries, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Chief Information`
  line `Commissioner and the Information Commissioners under sub-section (5) of section 13 and the State`
  line `Chief Information Commissioner and the State Information Commissioners under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 16;]`
  line
  line `(d) the salaries and allowances payable to and the terms and conditions of service of the officers`
  line `and other employees under sub-section (6) of section 13 and sub-section (6) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure to be adopted by the Central Information Commission or State Information`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, in deciding the appeals under sub-section (10) of section 19; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (10900)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make rules by competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10900&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The competent authority may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the cost of the medium or print cost price of the materials to be disseminated under sub-section`
  line `(4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(ii) the fee payable under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(iii) the fee payable under sub-section (1) of section 7; and`
  line
  line `(iv) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (10901)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Laying of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10901&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period`
  line `of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if,`
  line `before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act by a State Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `notified, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (10902)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10902&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removal of`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (10903)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title Repeal.
  content `The Freedom of Information Act, 2002 (5 of 2003) is hereby repealed.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955&sectionId=10903&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00004_200522_1517807322955
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
